<p>I came across this problem in my current project as I have quite a bit of JSON that requires some commenting to keep things easy to remember.</p>

<p>I've used this simple python function to replace comments &amp; use <code>json.loads</code> to convert it into a <code>dict</code>:</p>

<pre><code>import json, re

def parse_json(data_string):
  result = []
  for line in data_string.split("\n"):
    line = line.strip()
    if len(line) &lt; 1 or line[0:2] == "//":
      continue
    if line[-1] not in "\,\"\'":
      line = re.sub("\/\/.*?$", "", line)
    result.append(line)
  return json.loads("\n".join(result))

print(parse_json("""
{
  // This is a comment
  "name": "value" // so is this
  // "name": "value"
  // the above line gets removed
}
"""))
</code></pre>
